messages.body: $GS cash out and join us at Waitr? $WTRH

$BAC $MS  These two (and $GS) the ones to own as been rightfully saying... but now the first two trudging back to the morning open gap?  Incredibly compelling levels around BV/share... SCREAMING, DESK-POUNDING buys as they rocket off into resumed buyback aggression 1Q21.

All three companies have hit my PTs for 2020 -- several years in a row for that matter.  Those were $30+, $60+ and $250 back in pummeled lat March 2020.

My PTS for ye end 2021?  Starting at $35+, $75+ and $275+ for now -- likely to be revised upward as covid mess fades and the economy recovers... as long as the republicans hold the senate.

P.S. Some will recall my PT for $SIVB was $275... ahem, missed that by a ton of conservatism -- but that is now trading like it is a TSLA or SNOW (wildly overvalued and untethered hot air balloons).
